oai_dc:dc.dc:title: RISK EVALUATION AT DIQUE DEL OESTE BREAKWATER IN PALMA DE MALLORCA (SPAIN)
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Calcerrada, Elena
Díaz, Ana María
Balmaseda, Raquel
Galán, lvaro
Castillo, Carmen
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Breakwaters are subject to coastal storms but also to climate change. The stochastic nature of both wave loading and structural response is different nowadays (and in the near future) from those at the time they were designed and the main investments are related to conservation and maintenance. Therefore, an updated risk analysis is needed in order to decide about adaptation or mitigation actions.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 36 (2018): Proceedings of 36th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Baltimore, Maryland, 2018; risk.56
